I had entertained the idea of security and how you could use access lists,
but being new to the Internet and implementing a DNS has kept me busy enough
that I have'nt dealt with the idea of Controlling access to the data in the 
DNS. I'm not sure many people have ever thought about or cared about security
until the "last worm" episode. Maybeng the access list or other mechanisms with anyone who is 
interested - maybe an Internet group for security is in order- but as of
now I have not spent any amount of time dwelling on it.

